      <h1 class="heading-large">Connect to GovWifi using a Blackberry</h1>
      <p>If your device was made before October 2016, you're probably running the BlackBerry operating system (OS). Follow these instructions to connect to GovWifi.</p>

      <h2 class="heading-medium">Instructions</h2>
      <p>Once you have a GovWifi <%= link_to "username and password", "/about-govwifi/connect-to-govwifi" %>, follow the steps below.  Depending on your device, you may need to scroll down to see all the fields.</p>
      <p>Step 1 - Open your wifi settings. A list of wifi networks appears.</p>
      <p>Step 2 - Select <strong>GovWifi</strong>. A settings menu appears.</p>
      <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/blackberry-step-2.png", class: "img-fluid" %>
      <p>Step 3 - Enter the username and password you received by email or text.</p>
      <p>Step 4 - Select <strong>Advanced Options</strong></p>
      <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/blackberry-step-4.png", class: "img-fluid" %>
      <p>Step 5 - Scroll down. For <strong>Security Sub Type</strong>, select <strong>PEAP</strong>.</p>
      <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/blackberry-step-5.png", class: "img-fluid" %>
      <p>Step 6 - For <strong>CA Certificate</strong>, select the third listing for <strong>GeoTrust Primary Certification Authority</strong>.</p>
      <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/blackberry-step-6.png", class: "img-fluid" %>
      <p>Step 7 - Select <strong>Connect</strong> on the top right of the screen.</p>
      <p>You should now be connected to GovWifi.</p>
      <p><strong>Support</strong></p>
      <p>You may get a message that says 'Wi-Fi Connection Status, Attempt 1 of 3, Connecting to network' and another that says â€˜Acquiring IP address'.  You don't need to do anything.</p>

      <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/blackberry-step-7-a.png", class: "img-fluid" %>
      <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/blackberry-step-7-b.png", class: "img-fluid" %>

      <h2 class="heading-medium">BlackBerry Android</h2>
      <p>If your BlackBerry device uses Android, follow the <%= link_to "Android instructions", "/support/connect-to-govwifi-using-an-android-device" %>.</p>
